Date: 28 Dec 2006
From: Yvonne Whitfield (MOH)

I have been in touch with the Chair of our botulism lab
here. Apparently the information from the FDA website needs to be
updated. We have been discussing possible cases of adult colonization
botulism, which fits into that undetermined category. The
undetermined category no longer exists. It should be referred to as
adult colonization botulism. In some cases, both infant and adult
colonization botulism have been grouped together as colonization botulism.
--
Yvonne Whitfield
Senior Program Consultant
Enteric and Zoonotic Unit
Infectious Diseases Branch
Ontario Ministry of Health and Long-term Care
8th Floor, 5700 Yonge St., Toronto, ON , M2M 4K5
<yvonne.whitfield@ontario.ca>
